= Pulling Repeated Sections =

Scales leverages and extends Scalaz Iteratees to allow resuming an Iteratee.  This resuming action is simply returning the current value and the next continuation when done ([./doc/scales/utils/package.html#ResumableIter:ResumableIter%5bE,%20A%5d ResumableIter]).  The [./doc/scales/xml/package.html#iterate(List%5bQName%5d,Iterator%5bPullType%5d):FlatMapIterator%5bXmlPath%5d iterate function], as shown [PullParsing.html#Simple_Reading_Of_Repeated_Sections here], uses this approach to provide a single path repeating section.

